{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"20892056","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/20892056"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-11-07T13:28:24+10:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-11-07T13:28:24+10:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"56433"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/20892056/user","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/20892056/relationships/user"}},"questionSession":{"data":null,"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/20892056/questionSession","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/20892056/relationships/questionSession"}},"session":{"data":null,"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/20892056/session","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/20892056/relationships/session"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"21090"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/20892056/question","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/20892056/relationships/question"}},"bookmark":{"data":null,"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/20892056/bookmark","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/20892056/relationships/bookmark"}}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"21090","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/21090"},"relationships":{"attempts":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/21090/attempts","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/21090/relationships/attempts"}},"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"13965"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/21090/item","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/21090/relationships/item"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"120778"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/21090/activeRevision","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/21090/relationships/activeRevision"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"13965","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"packs":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/packs","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/relationships/packs"}},"revisions":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/revisions","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/relationships/revisions"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"21090"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/content","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/relationships/content"}},"specialtyTags":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/specialtyTags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/relationships/specialtyTags"}},"primaryTags":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/primaryTags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/relationships/primaryTags"}},"contributionTypes":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/contributionTypes","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/relationships/contributionTypes"}},"contributors":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/contributors","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/relationships/contributors"}},"contribution":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/contribution","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/relationships/contribution"}},"myContribution":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/myContribution","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/relationships/myContribution"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"102375"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/activeRevision","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/relationships/activeRevision"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"29"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"560"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"9485"}],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/tags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/relationships/tags"}},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"33693"},{"type":"contributions","id":"53204"}],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/contributions","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13965/relationships/contributions"}}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"120778","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/120778"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 52-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a slowly growing lump on her right flank that she first noticed approximately two years ago. The lesion is painless; however, she is concerned about the cosmetic impact. She has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. There is a 6 cm, soft, mobile, non-tender mass in the subcutaneous tissue of the right flank. The overlying skin appears normal. The mass is surgically excised and sent for histopathological examination. The specimen measures 21.5 \u00d7 13.5 cm and appears as a well-circumscribed, yellow, lobulated mass (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following pathological entities is most likely represented in the image?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Angiolipoma","Liposarcoma","Hibernoma","Lipoma","Sebaceous cyst"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe image shows a well-circumscribed, yellow, lobulated mass consistent with a lipoma. Lipomas are benign tumours composed of mature adipocytes (fat cells) and are the most common soft tissue tumours. They typically present as slow-growing, painless, soft, mobile masses in the subcutaneous tissue, exactly as described in this patient.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELipoma\u003C/strong\u003E is the correct diagnosis based on the clinical presentation and gross appearance. Histologically, lipomas consist of mature adipocytes with uniform nuclei pushed to the periphery of the cell, surrounded by a thin fibrous capsule. They are typically found in the subcutaneous tissues of the neck, back, shoulders, and flanks. The yellow, lobulated appearance and well-circumscribed nature seen in the image are characteristic features.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAngiolipoma\u003C/strong\u003E is a variant of lipoma that contains numerous small blood vessels. On gross examination, angiolipomas may appear more reddish or have visible blood vessels compared to the uniform yellow appearance of a typical lipoma. Clinically, angiolipomas are often painful, unlike the painless mass described in this patient.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELiposarcoma\u003C/strong\u003E is a malignant tumour of adipose tissue that can sometimes be difficult to distinguish from lipoma on gross examination. However, liposarcomas often have areas of haemorrhage, necrosis, or firmer tissue, and they tend to be less well-circumscribed. They are also less common than lipomas and would be unusual in this clinical context of a slow-growing, painless mass.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHibernoma\u003C/strong\u003E is a rare benign tumour composed of brown fat cells. Grossly, hibernomas appear tan to reddish-brown rather than the bright yellow colour of lipomas. They are much less common than lipomas and typically occur in areas where brown fat persists into adulthood, such as the interscapular region, neck, axilla, and thigh.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESebaceous cyst\u003C/strong\u003E (epidermal inclusion cyst) is a benign cyst filled with keratin debris. On gross examination, sebaceous cysts typically have a white, cheesy material inside and a thin wall. They are usually attached to the overlying skin and would not present as the yellow, lobulated mass seen in the image.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Lipomas are benign tumours composed of mature adipocytes that appear as well-circumscribed, yellow, soft masses.","Histologically, lipomas show mature adipocytes with uniform nuclei pushed to the periphery of the cell.","Lipomas are the most common soft tissue tumours, typically found in the subcutaneous tissue."],"references":["Uthman, Ed. Lipoma. Flikr. Accessed under license CC By 2.0: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/deed.en.  Accessed at: https://www.flickr.com/photos/euthman/52372956684/in/pool-labmed/","Renne SL. Lipoma. PathologyOutlines.com website. https://www.pathologyoutlines.com/topic/softtissueadiposelipoma.html. Accessed October 16th, 2025."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"102375"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/120778/itemRevision","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/120778/relationships/itemRevision"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"21090"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/120778/question","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/120778/relationships/question"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21825"}],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/120778/stemMedia","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/120778/relationships/stemMedia"}},"explanationMedia":{"data":[],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/120778/explanationMedia","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/120778/relationships/explanationMedia"}}}},{"type":"media","id":"21825","links":{"self":"https://ap